## Integration Test with inject

```typescript
describe('Resource Routes + Service', () => {
  let fastify: ReturnType<typeof Fastify>;

  beforeEach(async () => {
    fastify = Fastify();
    fastify.decorate('prisma', mockPrismaClient);
    fastify.register(resourceServicePlugin);
    fastify.register(resourceRoutes, { prefix: '/resources' });
    await fastify.ready();
  });

  afterEach(() => fastify.close());

  it('should fetch resource via endpoint', async () => {
    const response = await fastify.inject({
      method: 'GET',
      url: '/resources/1',
    });

    expect(response.statusCode).toBe(200);
  });
});
```

## Conventions
- Service is a pure class — test with `new` and simple mocks
- Plugin tested separately: verify decorator exists
- Integration tests with `fastify.inject()` when needed
- Always call `fastify.close()` after tests with Fastify
- Mock dependencies via `decorate` before registering plugin
- Separate unit tests (service) from integration tests (plugin + routes)
